I'm doing well, thanks for asking! I'm a large language model, so I don't have feelings like humans do, but I'm always happy to chat and help with any questions or tasks you have.

Now, about that code for a landing page of an AI agent making company... Here's a simple example in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript:

**HTML:**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Agenda - AI Agent Makers</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
                <li><a href="#services">Services</a></li>
                <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section id="hero">
            <h1>Agenda - Revolutionizing AI Agents</h1>
            <p>Transforming industries with intelligent automation</p>
            <button>Learn More</button>
        </section>
        <section id="about">
            <h2>About Us</h2>
            <p>We're a team of innovators passionate about creating AI agents that make a difference.</p>
        </section>
        <section id="services">
            <h2>Our Services</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>AI Agent Development</li>
                <li>Custom Solutions</li>
                <li>Consulting Services</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section id="contact">
            <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
            <p>Ready to transform your industry? Contact us today!</p>
            <form>
                <input type="email" placeholder="Email">
                <input type="phone" placeholder="Phone">
                <textarea placeholder="Message"></textarea>
                <button>Send</button>
            </form>
        </section>
    </main>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
**CSS (in style.css file):**
```css
body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

header {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    padding: 1em;
    text-align: center;
}

nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
}

nav li {
    margin-right: 20px;
}

nav a {
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
}

main {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    padding: 2em;
}

section {
    background-color: #f7f7f7;
    padding: 2em;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

h1, h2 {
    color: #333;
}

button {
    background-color: #333;
    color: #fff;
    border: none;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    font-size: 16px;
    cursor: pointer;
}

button:hover {
    background-color: #444;
}
```
**JavaScript (in script.js file):**
```javascript
// Add event listeners to navigation links
document.querySelectorAll('nav a').forEach(link => {
    link.addEventListener('click', event => {
        event.preventDefault();
        document.querySelector(link.getAttribute('href')).scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
    });
});
```
This code creates a basic landing page with a hero section, about section, services section, and contact section. The CSS adds some basic styling, and the JavaScript adds smooth scrolling to the navigation links. Of course, this is just a starting point, and you'll want to customize and expand upon this code to fit your company's specific needs.
